        "text": "He shall never see death - To see death, or to taste of death, is the same as to die, Luke 2:26; Matthew 16:28; Mark 9:1. The sense of this passage is, \"He shall obtain eternal life, or he shall be raised up to that life where there shall be no death.\" See John 6:49-50; John 3:36; John 5:24; John 11:25-26. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "He shall never see death - To see death, or to taste of death, is the same as to die, ",
